  <%# ─── Environment variables ─── %>

  <section class="prose-section" id="env-vars">
    <h2>Environment variables</h2>
    <p>These environment variables control CLI behavior and CI integration:</p>

    <dl class="docs-fields">
      <div class="docs-field">
        <dt><code>DEVOPSELLENCE_TOKEN</code></dt>
        <dd>API token for non-interactive authentication. Used in CI and automation.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-field">
        <dt><code>DEVOPSELLENCE_ORGANIZATION</code></dt>
        <dd>Override the organization slug (instead of reading from <code>devopsellence.yml</code>).</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-field">
        <dt><code>DEVOPSELLENCE_PROJECT</code></dt>
        <dd>Override the project slug.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-field">
        <dt><code>DEVOPSELLENCE_ENVIRONMENT</code></dt>
        <dd>Override the target environment.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-field">
        <dt><code>DEVOPSELLENCE_ENV_VARS</code></dt>
        <dd>JSON object of runtime environment variables to set during deploy. Flat <code>{"KEY":"val"}</code> or scoped <code>{"web":{"KEY":"val"}}</code>.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-field">
        <dt><code>DEVOPSELLENCE_SECRETS</code></dt>
        <dd>JSON object of secrets to set during deploy. Same format as <code>DEVOPSELLENCE_ENV_VARS</code>. Values are stored in Secret Manager.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-field">
        <dt><code>DEVOPSELLENCE_HETZNER_API_TOKEN</code></dt>
        <dd>Hetzner API token for <code>devopsellence node create</code>. <code>HCLOUD_TOKEN</code> is also supported.</dd>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-field">
        <dt><code>HCLOUD_TOKEN</code></dt>
        <dd>Alternative Hetzner API token variable used by the Hetzner CLI and supported by solo mode.</dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <%# ─── Migrating solo → shared ─── %>

  <section class="prose-section" id="migrating">
    <h2>Migrating from solo to shared</h2>
    <p>When you outgrow solo mode, switching to shared keeps most of your setup intact. The agent reconciliation loop, your <code>devopsellence.yml</code> config, your Dockerfile, and your deploy verbs all stay the same.</p>

    <h3>What changes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Mode</strong> &mdash; run <code>devopsellence mode use shared</code>, then <code>devopsellence setup</code> to sign in and create org/project/env context.</li>
      <li><strong>Nodes</strong> &mdash; register your existing servers with <code>devopsellence node register</code> and run the install command on each server. The agent switches from file-watching to control-plane polling.</li>
      <li><strong>Images</strong> &mdash; instead of streaming over SSH, images are pushed to a container registry. The control plane handles registry credentials.</li>
      <li><strong>Secrets</strong> &mdash; re-create secrets with <code>devopsellence secret set &lt;name&gt; --service web --stdin</code>. They move from your local <code>.env</code> to encrypted server-side storage.</li>
      <li><strong>Config</strong> &mdash; the <code>direct.nodes</code> block in <code>devopsellence.yml</code> is no longer used. You can remove it or leave it; the CLI ignores it in shared mode.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What stays the same</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Your <code>devopsellence.yml</code> app config (build, services, tasks, ingress, health checks, volumes).</li>
      <li>Your Dockerfile and application code.</li>
      <li>The agent's reconciliation loop, zero-downtime rollouts, health checks, and Envoy proxy.</li>
      <li>CLI verbs: <code>deploy</code>, <code>status</code>, <code>secret</code>, <code>doctor</code>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <%# ─── Troubleshooting ─── %>

  <section class="prose-section" id="troubleshooting">
    <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
    <p>Run <code>devopsellence doctor</code> first. Most first-deploy issues are local setup problems.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Docker not running?</strong> The CLI needs Docker to build images. Start Docker and try again.</li>
      <li><strong>Auth expired?</strong> Run <code>devopsellence auth login</code> to refresh, then <code>devopsellence doctor</code> to verify.</li>
      <li><strong>Deploy hangs?</strong> Check the deploy output. A failing health check or crashing container will stall the rollout. Fix the app and redeploy.</li>
      <li><strong>Release task failing?</strong> The command runs in a container with its configured service image. Check that migrations or setup scripts work with your current database state.</li>
      <li><strong>Node not picking up deploys?</strong> Run <code>devopsellence node diagnose &lt;id&gt;</code> to check agent status and connectivity. Verify the node is assigned to the correct environment.</li>
      <li><strong>Secrets not available?</strong> In shared mode, secrets are scoped to a service. Make sure you set the secret with the correct <code>--service</code> flag matching your service name (<code>web</code> or <code>worker</code>), then confirm with <code>devopsellence secret list</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Solo deploy transfer looks slow?</strong> The CLI prints compressed bytes while streaming the image over SSH. If it fails before transfer, run <code>devopsellence doctor</code> in a solo workspace and check SSH plus Docker or passwordless sudo access.</li>
      <li><strong>Solo Rails app missing <code>secret_key_base</code>?</strong> Put <code>RAILS_MASTER_KEY</code> in the solo <code>.env</code>, or keep <code>config/master.key</code> available locally during deploy.</li>
      <li><strong>Wrong environment or mode?</strong> Run <code>devopsellence context show</code> to see the current mode and target context. Check <code>default_environment</code> in your <code>devopsellence.yml</code> for the shared path.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Questions? <a href="mailto:<%= @contact_email %>"><%= @contact_email %></a></p>
  </section>

  <%# ─── Cleanup ─── %>

  <section class="prose-section" id="cleanup">
    <h2>Cleanup &amp; uninstall</h2>

    <h3>Remove a node</h3>
    <div class="terminal">
      <div class="terminal-bar">
        <span class="dot dot-red"></span>
        <span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
        <span class="dot dot-green"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body">
        <div class="tl"><span class="tp">$</span> devopsellence node detach 42</div>
        <div class="tl tl-muted"># Then on the server, run the agent uninstall:</div>
        <div class="tl"><span class="tp">$</span> <%= @agent_uninstall_command %></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Delete an environment</h3>
    <div class="terminal">
      <div class="terminal-bar">
        <span class="dot dot-red"></span>
        <span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
        <span class="dot dot-green"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body">
        <div class="tl"><span class="tp">$</span> devopsellence context env delete production</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Revoke tokens</h3>
    <div class="terminal">
      <div class="terminal-bar">
        <span class="dot dot-red"></span>
        <span class="dot dot-yellow"></span>
        <span class="dot dot-green"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body">
        <div class="tl"><span class="tp">$</span> devopsellence auth token list</div>
        <div class="tl"><span class="tp">$</span> devopsellence auth token revoke &lt;token-id&gt;</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
